Saying he had wanted to talk about the subject for years but feared it would damage his career, beloved entertainer Dick Van Dyke confessed Wednesday to being the infamous Zodiac Killer, the serial murderer who terrorized Northern California more than four decades ago.The 87-year-old actor, singer, comedian, and dancer, best known for his pioneering TV career and roles in films like  and , spoke at length with reporters about the ghoulish Bay Area execution-style murders, marveling at the fact that he was never caught.“I am the Zodiac,” said Van Dyke, using the pseudonym of the man who claimed to have killed 37 people and once dared authorities to find him as he continued to “collect slaves for the afterlife.” “The murders, the taunting calls to the police, the letters, the cryptograms sent to local newspapers—that was all me.